node.text: Nice to do something different and make some good family memories while at it. I could see myself doing a few more green wood projects here and there. Lovely, peaceful and rewarding work. If you ever see a Green wood class available in your area - jump on it, you’ll enjoy it!

node.text:
Finishing up the chair in the episode going up today! What a treat this has been to get to make a project alongside my Dad again in his wood shop. 
-
It’s got us thinking - maybe we need to get him into the forge for us to make him a knife together? 🧐🤓

node.text: Flash back to 13 year old me, 10 years ago, learning from Brian Brazeal. A pivotal moment for what would become my career. I learnt so much from this visit and subsequent ones and this knowledge is entirely how I got off the ground. His generosity with his knowledge is something I’ll always be grateful for.
